Laptop Battery Life and Charging Habits

This story will show the average battery life of my old laptop and my charging habits which I record everytime I reach over to turn on the charger.

Data of Recorded Charges

Here is a bar chart showing how many times I recorded the laptop charges by month:

Both March and May have 19 records each which seems about right considering that was during Project 2 and this current project respectively.

Battery Life

Now lets take a look at how long the laptop battery lasted.

It looks like that on average, the laptop battery lasts 1 hour 30 minutes with a maximum of 2 hours and a minimum of 1 hour. The battery must be pretty worn down if it only lasts that long but it is a 4 and half year old laptop after all.

Charging Habits - Battery Percentage

I tend to start charging the laptop battery the most at 21-30%. Though I do have battery saver mode automatically turn on at 30% which could have influenced when I started charging.

battery percent at beginning of charge

I seem to charge the battery up to 91-100% for over half my charges. Usually, I want charge to aroud 80% but clearly this data shows that I do not do a very good job at checking how the battery has charged.

I tend to drop the battery percent to 10% or below before I charge to laptop at 6pm to 10pm compared to the more varied times where I start charging above 10%.

time of charge and if charge was less than ten percent

Charging Habits - Time of Charge

I usually start charging at 10am, 2pm, 4pm, 5pm, and 9pm as I am most likely using the laptop during those times.

number of times charged at a specific hour
